y and event:listen patterns along with the readonly toggle JSP code example. All the expected hints are accounted for.\n\nFor s2, I'm verifying the condition, target, and reverse attributes are documented, along with the readonly attribute switching behavior, event action specifications, and the local rendering constraints—everything appears to be there.\n\nSince no_knowledge_content is set to false, I can skip that validation. One minor gap I'm noticing is that the introduction mentions support for checkboxes, radio buttons, and dropdown elements, but I should verify whether all three are equally covered throughout the documentation. The knowledge file completely omits which element types this widget supports, which is critical information for determining applicability. I'll flag this as a critical omission since it directly affects whether someone can use this widget for their needs.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13703,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":13703,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3f4eb5d5-b1ca-4ef1-a809-505458a014bc","uuid":"f90f4caa-6bc8-4099-9465-80e658eb1ea3"}
